1
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:25,733


2
00:01:19,410 --> 00:01:20,940
Yes, hello?

3
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:23,580
My name is Nase Izumi.

4
00:01:23,580 --> 00:01:25,780
Nase? The Nase?

5
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:27,020
Yes.

6
00:01:27,020 --> 00:01:30,110
I'm calling with some news for you.

7
00:02:37,940 --> 00:02:39,480
Kuriyama Mirai-san?

8
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:42,260
Pleased to meet you.

9
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:43,600
I'm Nase Izumi.

10
00:02:44,350 --> 00:02:45,480
This is Kuriyama Mirai.

11
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:48,730
A spirit hunter and legitimate successor of the cursed bloodline.

12
00:02:48,730 --> 00:02:54,330
Do you mean the clan that is
shunned by most spirit hunters?

13
00:02:54,330 --> 00:02:55,240
Yes.

14
00:02:55,810 --> 00:02:57,030
Kuriyama-san.

15
00:03:07,090 --> 00:03:10,230
She can use her own blood as a weapon.

16
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:16,350
Not only can it be hardened, it can also be used as a lethal poison that erodes bodily tissue.

17
00:03:16,350 --> 00:03:18,770
Will that be enough?

18
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:20,600
It's hard to say.

19
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,850
But I believe she stands a very good chance.

20
00:03:22,850 --> 00:03:26,510
Isn't the target said to be immortal?

21
00:03:26,510 --> 00:03:27,980
Yes.

22
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:29,580
Immortal?

23
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:34,210
In truth, he's just terrifyingly quick to recover,

24
00:03:34,210 --> 00:03:38,410
but he's known to the spirit hunters
around here as the "immortal half-shade."

25
00:03:39,230 --> 00:03:41,290
The immortal half-shade?

26
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:42,910
Let me show you.

27
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:51,220
\hUnlike shadelings, he's half human and half shade—a preposterous and dangerous being.

28
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:56,010
My research showed me that his shade half resembles the shade beyond the horizon.

29
00:03:56,010 --> 00:04:00,420
My younger brother attempted to kill this fellow
but had the tables turned on him.

30
00:04:00,420 --> 00:04:02,630
He nearly died from his injuries.

31
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:06,100
You're the only one I can count on.

32
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,690
Please.

33
00:04:08,890 --> 00:04:14,360
This is the shade from beyond the horizon?

34
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:19,560
Sorry for dragging you along to
that stifling meeting back there.

35
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:23,190
It may be because of this area's long history, but we have certain customs.

36
00:04:23,190 --> 00:04:24,520
Bonsai?

37
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,660
Yes.

38
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:26,940
Um, that aside...

39
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:27,850
What?

40
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:30,790
Where's this shade from beyond the horizon?

41
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:32,240
Rest assured.

42
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:34,230
He's under constant supervision.

43
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:37,340
I'll have to kill him sooner or later, right?

44
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:39,020
Then I'd prefer it to be sooner.

45
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:39,550
Can you?

46
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:43,220
How should I know?!

47
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,520
You had no idea either—

48
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:44,520
That's not it.

49
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:48,800
I'm asking you if you're mentally prepared for this.

50
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:03,370
The half-shade's name is Kanbara Akihito.

51
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,300
Suicide.

52
00:05:15,430 --> 00:05:21,900
Defined in the dictionary as "the act of taking one's own life,"

53
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:26,780
it's something I will probably never even think about doing.

54
00:05:28,610 --> 00:05:31,730
Not because I think it's unethical,

55
00:05:31,730 --> 00:05:35,280
but for a more fundamental reason.

56
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,940
However, let's save that for later.

57
00:05:38,590 --> 00:05:41,200
Right now, she's about to die.

58
00:05:42,310 --> 00:05:44,940
At least, it seemed like that to me.

59
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:50,240
At this point the story can proceed in one of two ways.

60
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:55,900
Either the protagonist plays an active role in the events that unfold,

61
00:05:55,900 --> 00:06:01,840
or he takes a passive role as the story moves on without him.

62
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:05,390
By all accounts, I'd fall into the latter category,

63
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:08,680
but for some reason, I chose the former option at this time.

64
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,520
H-Hey!

65
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:19,280
I won't repeat everything I said, but...

66
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:23,870
"...at any rate, someone who looks as good in glasses as you

67
00:06:23,870 --> 00:06:25,330
simply must not die!"

68
00:06:25,730 --> 00:06:28,700
That was my heartfelt plea to her.

69
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:33,920
I finished by screaming out everything I felt at that moment.

70
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:36,210
"Basically, I love glasses!"

71
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:39,090
How unpleasant.

72
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:50,730
You—

73
00:06:56,410 --> 00:06:58,850
You picked a fight with the wrong person.

74
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:03,420
Hey, uh...

75
00:07:03,420 --> 00:07:07,450
Think you could at least do something about this sword?

76
00:07:07,450 --> 00:07:09,410
Please?

77
00:07:13,890 --> 00:07:17,320
And that's how I met Kuriyama Mirai.

78
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:22,570
If our story had ended after a meeting like that,

79
00:07:22,570 --> 00:07:26,700
I don't think any story in this world would be worth telling.

80
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:34,060
Beyond the Boundary

81
00:07:50,910 --> 00:07:51,740
Did she give up?

82
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,580
Where did you even come from?!

83
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,650
Take this!

84
00:08:06,350 --> 00:08:08,160
Hey, we can't go around destroying buckets!

85
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,020
Jeez!

86
00:08:40,710 --> 00:08:43,170
I think it's about time we put an end to this.

87
00:08:44,310 --> 00:08:45,550
What is this, a horror movie?

88
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,660
E-Everything's dark!

89
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:51,640
What'd you do to me?!

90
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,840
It's just a bucket.

91
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,980
Are you hungry?

92
00:09:04,390 --> 00:09:05,650
What's the big deal?

93
00:09:05,650 --> 00:09:06,860
It's not like you lose anything!

94
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:08,220
Of course I do!

95
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:09,990
You keep chipping away at what's left of my heart!

96
00:09:09,990 --> 00:09:12,390
I told you I still feel pain, didn't I?!

97
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:14,550
Do you have any idea how much it hurts?

98
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:17,820
Doing whatever you please to us immortals
is just discrimination!

99
00:09:17,820 --> 00:09:19,170
People are going to hear you, you know.

100
00:09:19,170 --> 00:09:20,660
It's fine.

101
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:22,340
I already made sure no one else was around.

102
00:09:22,340 --> 00:09:24,380
Thanks for waiting.

103
00:09:24,380 --> 00:09:29,220
Here are your extra burrito, mole poblano, and chili con carne combos.

104
00:09:29,220 --> 00:09:30,680
Enjoy yourselves.

105
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,580
You ordered even more food?!

106
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:33,430
You're being unpleasant.

107
00:09:33,430 --> 00:09:35,980
I'm the one who's finding this unpleasant!

108
00:09:35,980 --> 00:09:37,660
Not only do you practice on me,

109
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:39,710
you even have the nerve to mooch off me for dinner!

110
00:09:39,710 --> 00:09:41,080
Mooch?

111
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,860
I thought we had a deal.

112
00:09:43,860 --> 00:09:46,860
I'd refrain from challenging you to any more fights tonight, and in exchange,

113
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,620
you'd treat me to dinner.

114
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:52,100
So that means you're going to attack me again tomorrow, I take it?

115
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,810
Why wouldn't I?

116
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,300
Kuriyama-san!

117
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,450
Are you alright?

118
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,370
I'm fine.

119
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:08,460
Just a little anemic.

120
00:10:08,460 --> 00:10:11,220
I was using my blood, after all.

121
00:10:13,610 --> 00:10:16,640
Let's take this to Ayaka-san tomorrow.

122
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:19,140
I'll come pick you up in the morning.

123
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,910
You shouldn't get too close to me.

124
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:25,840
I've unleashed powers I normally keep in check.

125
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:29,610
Immortal or not, you don't want to touch my blood right now.

126
00:10:29,610 --> 00:10:32,570
We still have to do something about that bleeding.

127
00:10:35,250 --> 00:10:36,650
Give me your hand.

128
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:40,200
I'll do it myself.

129
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,620
Come on.

130
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:48,550
Kuriyama-san, you haven't joined a club yet, have you?

131
00:10:48,550 --> 00:10:50,800
I don't have time for that.

132
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,800
I can't interest you in the Literature Club?

133
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:53,800
Why do you ask?

134
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:56,050
Because I'd love for a beauty with glasses to join.

135
00:10:56,050 --> 00:10:57,560
How unpleasant.

136
00:10:58,130 --> 00:11:00,410
Well, it's the club I'm in,

137
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:02,060
and we only have two real members right now.

138
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,520
Oh, and the other one's a spirit hunter too,

139
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:07,540
so I'm sure it'd work in your favor professionally as well.

140
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:11,010
I'll have to pass.

141
00:11:11,010 --> 00:11:12,700
Huh? Why?

142
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:15,950
I don't want to associate with other people...

143
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:25,840
I guess his immortality really can't
be dealt with using normal methods.

144
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,460
Yes.

145
00:11:27,100 --> 00:11:29,570
You should observe him for a while.

146
00:11:29,570 --> 00:11:33,390
Attacking him haphazardly won't get you anywhere.

147
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:33,930
But...

148
00:11:34,560 --> 00:11:39,510
In time, his shade half is sure to surface again,
as it did against Hiro'omi.

149
00:11:39,980 --> 00:11:42,090
Use that opportunity.

150
00:11:42,090 --> 00:11:43,310
Okay.

151
00:11:43,730 --> 00:11:45,050
Also...

152
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:48,270
Let me offer you a warning.

153
00:11:48,940 --> 00:11:52,380
You'd be better off keeping
your distance from Akihito-kun.

154
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:55,260
Oh, right.

155
00:11:55,260 --> 00:11:56,110
Kuriyama-san.

156
00:11:56,110 --> 00:11:57,120
Y-Yes?

157
00:11:57,120 --> 00:12:00,050
Remember what we talked about yesterday? How about it?

158
00:12:00,050 --> 00:12:03,000
I want to invite her to come visit the Literature Club. Is that okay?

159
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:05,290
She says she hasn't joined any clubs,

160
00:12:05,290 --> 00:12:08,240
and there aren't many other spirit hunters at our school.

161
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,500
Besides, she only just got here—

162
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,630
I thought I refused already.

163
00:12:16,180 --> 00:12:17,430
I'm scared.

164
00:12:18,210 --> 00:12:20,070
I'm terrified of taking lives.

165
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,640
Then why don't you quit being a spirit hunter?

166
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:27,130
If I could...

167
00:12:27,130 --> 00:12:29,560
If I could, I would've done so a long time ago!

168
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:32,260
I tried to quit!

169
00:12:32,260 --> 00:12:33,770
I tried to quit being a spirit hunter,

170
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:35,900
quit killing dreamshades,

171
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:37,740
and live a normal life!

172
00:12:38,830 --> 00:12:41,990
But this cursed blood flowing through my veins is anything but normal.

173
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:44,880
This power of mine...

174
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:48,120
The same goes for me.

175
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:59,050
Why would you say that?

176
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:01,020
Why...

177
00:13:03,070 --> 00:13:05,810
You're an investigator from the Spirit Hunter Association's Observation Bureau?

178
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:06,870
That's right.

179
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:10,970
I'm Fujima Miroku. Nice to meet you, Nase Izumi-san.

180
00:13:10,970 --> 00:13:13,070
So, what is your business here?

181
00:13:13,070 --> 00:13:15,410
The Hollow Shadow.

182
00:13:15,410 --> 00:13:18,700
Dreamshades this powerful don't show up too often,

183
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:20,700
so I'm here to observe it.

184
00:13:21,940 --> 00:13:23,950
Dreams mark the way to the underworld.

185
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:29,710
And we call the darkness that lies within them "dreamshades," masses of human resentment

186
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:34,760
brought to life by the twisted human heart and all of its hatred, envy, and aggression.

187
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:38,070
Dreamshades will continue to exist as long as humans do.

188
00:13:38,070 --> 00:13:40,970
So long as we can see them, we will continue to kill them.

189
00:13:40,970 --> 00:13:44,440
Doesn't that make you feel like spirit hunting thrives on the misery of others?

190
00:13:48,330 --> 00:13:50,480
I see you have some interesting views on the subject.

191
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,190
How so?

192
00:13:53,190 --> 00:13:59,330
Having descended from a long line of spirit hunters
that have been fighting shades since antiquity,

193
00:13:59,330 --> 00:14:01,540
I see shades the same way a farmer sees rice,

194
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:03,940
or a fisherman sees fish.

195
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:06,350
It doesn't matter what they are.

196
00:14:06,350 --> 00:14:07,820
I see.

197
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:11,270
May I ask you something?

198
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,250
Go ahead.

199
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,750
What are dreamshades to you?

200
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:18,760
That goes without saying, doesn't it?

201
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:21,760
Monsters, nothing more.

202
00:14:23,010 --> 00:14:23,760
Do I...

203
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,930
look like a normal person...

204
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:29,670
to you?

205
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:36,770
In my eyes,

206
00:14:36,770 --> 00:14:40,280
you're nothing but a bespectacled beauty.

207
00:14:48,850 --> 00:14:50,700
What... the...

208
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:54,130
The Hollow Shadow?

209
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:05,640
Kuriyama-san...

210
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,300
Hurry up...

211
00:15:08,650 --> 00:15:09,520
And stab me!

212
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:13,400
It's in a weakened state right now, isn't it?

213
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:17,280
Chase it out of my body and you'll be able to finish it off!

214
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:18,730
But you'll...

215
00:15:18,730 --> 00:15:20,830
I won't die.

216
00:15:20,830 --> 00:15:22,320
I'm immortal, after all.

217
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:28,910
I won't last much longer.

218
00:15:29,350 --> 00:15:30,250
Hurry up!

219
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:31,290
B-But...

220
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:34,670
Isn't this what you came here to do?

221
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:38,060
Didn't you come here telling yourself you had to do this?

222
00:15:38,060 --> 00:15:40,170
Y-Yes, but...

223
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:42,470
Then don't falter now!

224
00:15:42,470 --> 00:15:44,480
Killing it won't change anything.

225
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:47,920
Not the blood flowing through your veins, nor the position you find yourself in.

226
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:49,810
It won't change a single thing!

227
00:15:50,180 --> 00:15:54,100
But you still came here!

228
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,190
So finish the job!

229
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:57,560
Don't give in to the Hollow Shadow!

230
00:15:58,120 --> 00:16:01,610
Otherwise everything you've done
will have been in vain!

231
00:16:01,610 --> 00:16:02,400
Stab me!

232
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,570
I'm immortal.

233
00:16:06,830 --> 00:16:07,410
So...

234
00:16:07,860 --> 00:16:09,020
So...

235
00:16:11,260 --> 00:16:12,410
live on!

236
00:16:13,260 --> 00:16:14,570
Senpai...

237
00:16:26,210 --> 00:16:28,090
Unleash your blood.

238
00:16:39,730 --> 00:16:40,420
Goodbye.

239
00:17:22,210 --> 00:17:23,090
Senpai...

240
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,070
Hold it.

241
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:28,110
Stay back.

242
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:40,790
What's wrong with you?

243
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,670
You went up against the Hollow Shadow, you know?

244
00:17:42,670 --> 00:17:44,730
Didn't you realize this was going to happen?

245
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:47,300
Forgive me.

246
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:49,950
I can't guarantee you'll survive this.

247
00:17:49,950 --> 00:17:51,180
I know.

248
00:18:02,660 --> 00:18:04,860
You know that Kanbara-kun's a half-shade, don't you?

249
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:07,830
When his body falls into a perilous state,

250
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:10,110
his shade half awakens.

251
00:18:12,270 --> 00:18:14,490
Basically, this is big trouble.

252
00:18:47,070 --> 00:18:49,360
Sen... pai...

253
00:18:54,830 --> 00:18:55,830
The cage!

254
00:18:55,830 --> 00:18:57,620
He can negate our spirit powers.

255
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:58,710
Ayaka-san!

256
00:18:58,710 --> 00:18:59,410
I know.

257
00:19:10,530 --> 00:19:11,760
Oh no!

258
00:19:22,930 --> 00:19:24,400
No way.

259
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,860
Nino-san!

260
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,630
This'll only hold him for a little while.

261
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:33,650
Now's our chance!

262
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,060
This isn't working!

263
00:19:43,460 --> 00:19:44,750
He's going to break out!

264
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,410
Do I...

265
00:20:20,110 --> 00:20:22,370
look like a normal person...

266
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:24,620
to you?

267
00:20:26,370 --> 00:20:28,460
The same goes for me.

268
00:20:30,980 --> 00:20:32,580
I'm sorry.

269
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:36,940
I didn't understand a thing about you,

270
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:39,560
and yet I...

271
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:42,560
I have to stop you.

272
00:21:26,390 --> 00:21:27,350
Kuriyama-san?

273
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:41,820
I did it again...

274
00:21:43,490 --> 00:21:45,100
She's...

275
00:21:56,610 --> 00:21:57,970
Senpai.

276
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:00,720
Sorry.

277
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:08,080
I'm so sorry!

278
00:22:15,770 --> 00:22:17,030
King of Chinese

279
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:17,030
Thanks for the food!

280
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:21,840
Slow down and savor it.

281
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,290
I feel like I don't have nearly enough blood!

282
00:22:24,290 --> 00:22:26,180
I need to replenish my iron.

283
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:28,660
Besides, I can't believe this isn't the Hollow Shadow,

284
00:22:29,660 --> 00:22:32,940
Or that it's only worth 200 yen!

285
00:22:32,940 --> 00:22:35,290
I don't think Ayaka-san would lie, though.

286
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:37,250
Then what's going on?

287
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:41,010
How would I know?

288
00:22:46,350 --> 00:22:49,740
Aren't you going to eat?

289
00:22:50,320 --> 00:22:50,850
Nah.

290
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:55,050
Where are you going?

291
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:55,990
The restroom.

292
00:22:58,800 --> 00:22:59,910
Hey...

293
00:22:59,910 --> 00:23:00,240
Yes?

294
00:23:00,910 --> 00:23:04,490
Do I look like a normal person to you?

295
00:23:08,850 --> 00:23:10,250
Let's see...

296
00:23:11,220 --> 00:23:14,670
In my eyes, you're nothing but an
ill-mannered guy who's obsessed with glasses.

297
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:20,800
What the heck?

298
00:23:43,910 --> 00:23:46,280
I've given it some thought since then.

299
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:48,200
I realized I shouldn't hesitate

300
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:54,210
\hand that I have to defeat Senpai—
the shade from beyond the horizon.

301
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:56,500
But I...

302
00:23:57,260 --> 00:24:03,260
I don't want to kill Senpai.

303
00:24:04,030 --> 00:24:06,720
I don't want to... kill him.

304
00:24:10,620 --> 00:24:16,060
I heard that the lull doesn't
actually begin until midnight,

305
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:21,820
but for some reason, I sense tension in the air.

306
00:24:23,970 --> 00:24:27,160
It's more stagnant than tense, if you ask me.

307
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:28,290
Lull, eh?

308
00:24:28,290 --> 00:24:29,580
The name fits perfectly.

309
00:24:30,180 --> 00:24:35,080
I should probably walk home
with my little sister right now.

310
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:37,790
She's long gone, though.

311
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:38,960
Why?!

312
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:40,790
Because she doesn't want to
walk home with you.

313
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:41,930
Why?!

314
00:24:41,930 --> 00:24:43,170
Because she hates you.

315
00:24:43,170 --> 00:24:44,240
Why?!

316
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:45,880
Because you keep acting like that all the time!

317
00:24:46,390 --> 00:24:51,110
Senpai, I'd better hurry or I won't make it in time for the supermarket's packed meals sale!

318
00:24:51,110 --> 00:24:52,970
Oh, okay.

319
00:24:52,970 --> 00:24:53,720
Later!

320
00:24:55,050 --> 00:24:56,320
Akkey.

321
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:59,420
Don't take this lightly.

322
00:24:59,420 --> 00:25:00,560
I'm feeling strangely nervous.

323
00:25:02,780 --> 00:25:04,030
Sounds like love.

324
00:25:19,170 --> 00:25:20,790
Want a ride?

325
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,050
I'll give you one.

326
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:28,800
A lull, huh?

327
00:25:33,230 --> 00:25:34,430
Why are you here?

328
00:25:34,820 --> 00:25:38,560
I figured we could talk a bit while I drive.

329
00:25:43,340 --> 00:25:45,310
Is that a dreamshade?

330
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:46,470
Yes.

331
00:25:46,470 --> 00:25:52,820
Just like the Hollow Shadow, there are many powerful shades that lack a physical form.

332
00:25:53,890 --> 00:25:59,700
They say this shade was born from all the resentment shown by humans over the years.

333
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:02,430
It is an entity formed from accumulated malice.

334
00:26:02,430 --> 00:26:08,910
Apparently it'll lead the world to ruin
if left alone, or something.

335
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:16,350
This dreamshade, said to be the cause of disease, war, and natural disasters,

336
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:19,890
is also commonly referred to as "the one beyond the horizon."

337
00:26:21,160 --> 00:26:25,110
Thankfully, only a fraction of it has shown up so far—

338
00:26:25,110 --> 00:26:26,360
not enough to be harmful.

339
00:26:27,090 --> 00:26:29,400
Why would you tell me this?

340
00:26:29,910 --> 00:26:34,700
We believe you Nases have the information we need, but you aren't very willing to share.

341
00:26:35,110 --> 00:26:38,420
So I thought I'd try to get it from you.

342
00:26:38,420 --> 00:26:41,690
Looks like they haven't told you anything, though.

343
00:26:42,690 --> 00:26:43,920
Yakiimo.

344
00:26:46,260 --> 00:26:47,500
It's the truth!

345
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:52,930
So, what is being done about this shade from beyond the horizon?

346
00:26:52,930 --> 00:26:56,350
Do you mean to tell me we Nases have been preparing in secret?

347
00:26:58,430 --> 00:27:00,100
Do you want to know that badly?

348
00:27:05,190 --> 00:27:09,320
Does Kuriyama-san have anything to do with
the shade from beyond the horizon?

349
00:27:09,830 --> 00:27:10,860
Beats me.

350
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:14,450
But it would be amusing if it did,

351
00:27:14,450 --> 00:27:15,160
don't you agree?

352
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:23,830
Bro!

353
00:27:24,290 --> 00:27:25,670
Oh dear.

354
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:35,220
You tailed your little sister all the way here?

355
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:37,220
It's almost like you have a thing for her.

356
00:27:37,220 --> 00:27:38,960
How you wound me.

357
00:27:38,960 --> 00:27:40,740
The "almost like" part was unnecessary!

358
00:27:47,320 --> 00:27:48,360
What are you after?

359
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:51,070
Ask your little sister.

360
00:27:58,870 --> 00:28:00,370
Onii-chan!

361
00:28:02,770 --> 00:28:05,960
That was a wonderful display of love for your brother.

362
00:28:13,940 --> 00:28:16,970
Wh-What the heck?

363
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:21,940
Akihito-kun was run over...

364
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:23,270
...so why isn't he hurt?

365
00:28:23,270 --> 00:28:24,370
Huh?

366
00:28:24,370 --> 00:28:25,030
Oh, well...

367
00:28:25,030 --> 00:28:27,230
Don't kill us!

368
00:28:27,230 --> 00:28:29,520
Please, don't kill us!

369
00:28:30,610 --> 00:28:33,460
Why would you say that?

370
00:28:53,890 --> 00:28:55,130
Izumi-san?

371
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,300
You must be worn out.

372
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:02,850
Why are you here?

373
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:08,230
Get some more rest.

374
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,800
Thank you for riding with us today.

375
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:18,800
This is Hananodera Station.

376
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:22,200
Please make sure you have all your belongings.

377
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:28,210
The obvious conclusion is that the lull's taking its toll on him.

378
00:29:28,630 --> 00:29:34,470
But I have a feeling that it severely weakened
not only his shade half, but also his human half.

379
00:29:34,470 --> 00:29:37,260
Isn't there any way to make him better?

380
00:29:38,070 --> 00:29:41,680
