569
00:41:21,670 --> 00:41:23,950
Well, I didn't ask you to put it on!

570
00:41:23,950 --> 00:41:24,910
Jeez.

571
00:41:24,910 --> 00:41:26,060
Akihito.

572
00:41:26,060 --> 00:41:26,590
What?

573
00:41:26,590 --> 00:41:30,850
Learn from this and take a long, hard look at yourself.

574
00:41:30,850 --> 00:41:35,470
I never want to go through anything like this again.

575
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:40,100
Okay.

576
00:41:40,100 --> 00:41:43,900
Also, drag that pervert over there back to the clubroom with you.

577
00:41:43,900 --> 00:41:45,110
Hey, pervert.

578
00:41:45,750 --> 00:41:47,570
What, pervert?

579
00:41:50,050 --> 00:41:53,110
The days are getting shorter and shorter, aren't they?

580
00:41:53,110 --> 00:41:55,580
Well, the summer solstice was back in June.

581
00:41:55,580 --> 00:41:57,070
Want to read some more before we go?

582
00:41:57,070 --> 00:41:58,160
No.

583
00:41:58,160 --> 00:42:01,310
Hiro'omi and Mitsuki sure are taking their time.

584
00:42:01,310 --> 00:42:02,580
They've already left.

585
00:42:02,580 --> 00:42:03,610
What?!

586
00:42:03,610 --> 00:42:07,800
Is that any way to treat someone who
just came back from the brink of death?

587
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:10,090
Isn't that exactly why?

588
00:42:10,090 --> 00:42:13,170
I'm sure they just don't know how to face you.

589
00:42:15,220 --> 00:42:16,350
What's wrong?

590
00:42:16,350 --> 00:42:18,240
N-Nothing.

591
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,190
Are you free after this, Kuriyama-san?

592
00:42:24,420 --> 00:42:27,530
I thought maybe we could get some dinner on the way back.

593
00:42:27,530 --> 00:42:29,740
Oh, if you're broke, I'll pay.

594
00:42:29,740 --> 00:42:31,110
R-Right...

595
00:42:31,110 --> 00:42:35,950
I mean, I don't remember what happened,
but I'm sure I caused you no end of trouble.

596
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:44,840
I wish you'd brought it up a little earlier.

597
00:42:44,840 --> 00:42:45,590
Today's no good?

598
00:42:45,590 --> 00:42:47,680
No.

599
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:51,300
This will probably end once the sun goes down.

600
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:53,090
What do you mean?

601
00:42:55,130 --> 00:42:56,560
Why...

602
00:42:56,560 --> 00:43:00,560
Why are you so nice to me?

603
00:43:05,400 --> 00:43:08,230
Because we're kinda similar.

604
00:43:09,370 --> 00:43:11,700
If I said that, would you get ma—

605
00:43:12,390 --> 00:43:13,930
Is it that insulting?!

606
00:43:13,930 --> 00:43:16,090
I-It's not like that!

607
00:43:16,090 --> 00:43:18,800
You look like you can't stand
the very thought of it!

608
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:20,370
D-Does that make you happy?

609
00:43:20,370 --> 00:43:21,500
Why would it?

610
00:43:21,500 --> 00:43:28,900
Well, Mitsuki-senpai told me that you
take extreme pleasure in being bullied,

611
00:43:28,900 --> 00:43:31,920
but I guess it's not that simple.

612
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:33,800
I'm glad it isn't!

613
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:35,720
Forget everything Mitsuki told you.

614
00:43:35,720 --> 00:43:37,140
I don't want to!

615
00:43:37,140 --> 00:43:39,050
I won't forget.

616
00:43:39,850 --> 00:43:41,400
I won't ever forget.

617
00:43:46,150 --> 00:43:48,020
What is this?

618
00:43:49,040 --> 00:43:50,500
It's you.

619
00:43:51,030 --> 00:43:53,030
The shade beyond the horizon—

620
00:43:53,030 --> 00:43:58,410
a coalescence of human malice that
\hthey say could lead the world to ruin—

621
00:43:59,250 --> 00:44:02,920
was the dreamshade within you.

622
00:44:02,920 --> 00:44:04,790
That's me?

623
00:44:05,340 --> 00:44:10,420
The whole reason I came to this town was to kill it.

624
00:44:11,470 --> 00:44:14,260
But that didn't go too well.

625
00:44:15,240 --> 00:44:18,340
I simply couldn't bring myself to kill you.

626
00:44:18,340 --> 00:44:19,930
I didn't want to kill you.

627
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:21,270
So I...

628
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:35,000
When I heard that I could use my blood

629
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:39,120
to drive the shade from beyond the horizon
out of you during the lull,

630
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:42,200
I decided I had to do it at any cost.

631
00:44:53,950 --> 00:44:57,140
What happened to you?

632
00:44:57,140 --> 00:44:57,840
I disappeared.

633
00:44:58,970 --> 00:44:59,390
Then...

634
00:45:00,170 --> 00:45:03,000
Then who is this sitting in front of me?

635
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:05,890
You haven't regained consciousness yet.

636
00:45:06,890 --> 00:45:11,080
This is all a dream.

637
00:45:11,080 --> 00:45:16,650
The little bit of my blood that's still within you
is what's showing you this dream.

638
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:22,870
But it's all over now.

639
00:45:22,870 --> 00:45:25,920
You'll wake up soon.

640
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:26,660
Kuriyama-san...

641
00:45:42,990 --> 00:45:46,200
I thought it'd be easier in a dream,

642
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:48,350
